          "date": "2013-04-08 06:22:51.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-790 obdclass: Removed hardcoded \"kernel: patchless_client\".",
        "message": "LU-790 obdclass: Removed hardcoded \"kernel: patchless_client\".\n\nCurrently patchless_client is hardcoded in the\nobd_proc_read_version() function. patchless_client means client does\nnot use any VFS patches. The earlier clients use to report here what\nkernel patch were applied. Since all lustre clients are patchless we\ncan remove the \"kernel: patchless_client\" string altogether.\nRemoved check_kernel_version() function from lustre/tests/sanity.sh\nwhich uses \"lctl get_param -n version\" output to get the kernel\npatch version. Now as all the clients are patchless the\ncheck_kernel_version() would always return true so no need to keep\nit around.\n\nSigned-off-by: Manisha Salve <msalve@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I6bbb9e5ea92b883bff8cf1e0454a660a5a58ec72\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
